snippet.textDisplay:
Hello guys! I've just discovered your channel and I'm already addicted to it. I'm a huge fan of movies in general, but especially scifi, horror, fantasy and movies that are visually appealing in general.
I love your VFX reaction videos, not just because they're funny, but they are so illustrative and helps non VFX workers kinda learn how this world works.
I have plenty of scenes, bad and good, that I'd love to recommend for your videos. But right now off the top of my head, I remember two scenes in Terminator 3: Rise of the machines (very underrated movie) that I loved back in the day:
- The fight between Schwarzenegger and the Terminatrix inside of a wc.
- The car chase, that involves a gigantic tow truck driven by the Terminatrix.
I haven't seen the movie in a long time, I hope it aged well.
Thank u for your videos and greetings from Spain!

snippet.textDisplay:
TL;DR React to the Practice of Closing Studios in the Animation/VFX industry

Since you guys reacted to Cats and the Sonic redesign, I'd love to see y'all react to the news that the studio that worked/crunched on those films (MPC Vancouver) closed shortly after (which you can read about here): https://www.kotaku.co.uk/2019/12/12/the-animation-studio-behind-the-sonic-the-hedgehog-redesign-has-shut-down

And then there was that snub from James Corden and Rebel Wilson at the oscars:
https://www.theguardian.com/film/shortcuts/2020/feb/13/why-james-corden-and-rebel-wilson-should-have-stuck-up-for-cats
https://twitter.com/YvesTM/status/1227092859565641728?s=20

Upvote if you agree, or downvote if I'm dumb and it's a silly idea
